{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, a regulator might only need to ensure that model performance does not significantly differ between two subpopulations.",
    "This does not necessarily demand that the interpretation elucidate the precise cause of each decision.",
    "Moreover, our broad definition does not restrict the interpretability method to explain the full system, but rather, only a mechanism within it.",
    "For example, developers might want to gain insights about specific components of the system to improve or modify their functionality.",
    "Miller (2017) and Lipton (2018) rightfully emphasize that interpretability should not be confused with an explanation."
  ]
}